headline: Did Walmart’s RFID Partnership Just Shift Avery Dennison’s (AVY) Fresh Food Innovation Narrative?
summary: Walmart recently announced a collaboration with Avery Dennison to expand the use of RFID technology in fresh food categories, targeting reduced food waste and improved inventory management across bakery, meat, and deli departments. This partnership signals a push toward greater supply chain transparency and efficiency, highlighting growing retailer demand for advanced digital identification solutions in perishable goods. headline: Nvidia earnings, FOMC minutes, Sept. jobs report: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Myles Udland previews several of the biggest stories to come throughout next week, including quarterly earnings results from major companies like Nvidia (NVDA), Home Depot (HD), Target (TGT), and Walmart (WMT); the latest round of commentary from top Federal Reserve officials alongside the minutes from the central bank's October FOMC meeting; and the release of the long-awaited September jobs report scheduled for Thursday, November 20. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
